en_179954_0	Six navy personnel including the former spokesperson Commodore D. K. P. Dassanayake who are in remand custody were re-remanded until 16th of this month today (Jan. 02).
en_179954_1	The remand term was extended when they were produced before Colombo Fort Magistrate, Lanka Jayaratne.
en_179954_2	They are accused of their alleged involvement in the abduction and disappearance of 11 youths in 2008.
en_179954_3	The Magistrate also ordered to issue an open warrant to arrest Lt. Commander Chandana Hettiarachchi who is also mentioned as a suspect in this case.
en_179954_4	Meanwhile, the Hiru Correspondent said D. M. Wijekanthan, a witness in this case, who was attached to the Army Intelligence Unit had made a 'closed door' statement to the Magistrate.
en_179954_5	It was allowed following a request made by his attorney.
